<subSubSection id="C8DF57105904C74CF56A70B8F7A5F701" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph id="44DF83B23D5D2C2308EAD7A43E3DA84F" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D85ABDC88FE9F9392F0E1698376EADC4" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Species complex. The taxonomy of the species is confused, with a long list of synonyms. Originally described from the Northern Adriatic but reported from worldwide locations (
<bibRefCitation id="0B4B47A8C6DFC57096109365C6F40B6C" author="Martin, Daniel" journalOrPublisher="Hydrobiologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="145 - 162" title="Inter-population variability and character description in the sponge-associated Haplosyllisspongicola complex (Polychaeta: Syllidae)" volume="496" year="2003">
<normalizedToken id="5CB0FED73CA260800DFEF0DD827DB4AC" originalValue="Martín">Martin</normalizedToken>
et al. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
), with three different morphotypes in the Western Mediterranean. Currently, three well-described species of 
<taxonomicName id="4B389D69240BBBA92562A7A6193165C1" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplosyllis" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Haplosyllis</taxonomicName>
are known the Mediterranean: 
<taxonomicName id="26D25F8AAFE5FB69DF423A5BBD8B32B2" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplosyllis spongicola" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="spongicola">Haplosyllis spongicola</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="BAF48083BFC9D8E1BDB167DF188C8861" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplosyllis" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Haplosyllis</taxonomicName>
chamaeleon Laubier, 1960 and 
<taxonomicName id="4AB85454AA70D269AB8925D3606945C3" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplosyllis granulosa" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="granulosa">Haplosyllis granulosa</taxonomicName>
(Lattig, San 
<normalizedToken id="88E4839723EAE6132C2F83FA3F59EB18" originalValue="Martín">Martin</normalizedToken>
&amp; Martin, 2007). The description of 
<taxonomicName id="FAD322101E5B312DBB4904EC811800A0" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplosyllis spongicola" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="spongicola">Haplosyllis spongicola</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="4C2CF9ECC3953C1A31C94C6F67A8BC3A" author="San Martin, G." journalOrPublisher="Fauna Iberica" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination=": 544 pp" title="AnnelidaPolychaeta II: Syllidae. In: Ramos MA, et al. (Eds)" volume="21, Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales, CA, SAIC, Madrid" year="2003">
San 
<normalizedToken id="361CB0FD1DD44FCEDF9DCBD229D93453" originalValue="Martín">Martin</normalizedToken>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
is referred in part to 
<taxonomicName id="44C0A7A01F7090E905159EAF5D35FB36" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplosyllis granulosa" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="granulosa">Haplosyllis granulosa</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="DF247AFFDF01A8F9C1EEBC32DA6E4FD1" author="Lattig, Patricia" journalOrPublisher="Scientia Marina" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="551 - 570" title="Taxonomic and morphometric analyses of the Haplosyllisspongicola complex (Polychaeta: Syllidae: Syllinae) from Spanish seas, with re-description of the type species and descriptions of two new species" volume="71" year="2007">Lattig et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, a number of 
<taxonomicName id="B9B6DFBC1226A630314D74BA8B4083D0" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplosyllis" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Haplosyllis</taxonomicName>
species have been described from the Mediterranean and the Black Sea which are currently regarded as incertae sedis due to lost type material and insufficient descriptions (
<bibRefCitation id="3E62E610D9A60A37B06440AE5B0986E6" author="Lattig, Patricia" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="1 - 40" title="A taxonomic revision of the genus Haplosyllis Langerhans, 1887 (Polychaeta, Syllidae, Syllinae)" volume="2220" year="2009">
Lattig and 
<normalizedToken id="811087556D42D1CED85D96F8E4DA6DEA" originalValue="Martín">Martin</normalizedToken>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
). Eastern Mediterranean records should also be examined for possible occurrences of the Red Sea species 
<taxonomicName id="49E2A08FD42953DFFAD0D60B3431C614" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Haplosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplosyllis djiboutiensis" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="djiboutiensis">Haplosyllis djiboutiensis</taxonomicName>
Gravier, 1900.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
